# Issue #1099: a generic `g[T]` forwarding to a bounded `f[T: Eq]`
# carries no constraint of its own — the check defers to `g`s
# instantiation. Instantiated at `Int` (which has `Eq`), the whole
# chain type-checks and runs, proving the deferral does not
# over-reject.

fn f[T: Eq](xs: [T]) : Int = 0
fn g[T](xs: [T]) : Int = f(xs)

fn main() : Int = {
  print(int_to_string(g([1, 2, 3])))
  0
}
